title: SFH to go on four-nation tour
content_text:
p>
    The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, will visit Canada, Chile 
    and Brazil and attend the World Health Assembly in Geneva, Switzerland, 
    between May 2 and 16. At his first stop in Toronto, Canada, Dr Chow will call on senior officials 
    of the Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care and the Ontario Ministry of 
    Agriculture, Food and Rural Affairs as well as representatives of local 
    medical professionals. During his stay in Toronto, Dr Chow will visit various medical facilities

medical professionals. During his stay in Toronto, Dr Chow will visit various medical facilities 
    and organisations including the Hospital for Sick Children, the Mount Sinai 
    Hospital and Samuel Lunenfeld Research Institute, the Krembil Neuroscience 
    Centre as well as the Regent Park Community Health Centre. He will also tour the Canada Health Infoway, an independent not-for-profit 
    corporation to foster and accelerate the development and adoption of 
    electronic health record systems, and the Guelph Food Technology Centre 
    which is an accredited organisation to deliver food safety audits and

which is an accredited organisation to deliver food safety audits and 
    certification services. From Toronto, Dr Chow will travel to Santiago, Chile, on May 5. He will 
    study the fishery and agricultural development in Chile by meeting officials 
    of the Ministry of Agriculture, the National Marine Fisheries Service and 
    the Agricultural and Livestock Service. He will also visit a salmon 
    technology institute, some salmon farms and fruit processing facilities.  Dr Chow will be in Brazil on May 8 and start his programme there by visiting

the Brazilian Agricultural Research Corporation. In addition to meetings at 
    the Brazilian Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Food Supply and the 
    Brazilian Meat Exporters Association, he will also visit cattle and poultry 
    farms to see the latest developments of the poultry industry in the country. After Brazil, Dr Chow will head for Geneva, the last leg of his visit. He 
    will meet the Minister of Health, Dr Chen Zhu, and the Director-General of 
    the World Health Organisation, Dr Margaret Chan, before attending the World

the World Health Organisation, Dr Margaret Chan, before attending the World 
    Health Assembly on May 16. He will return to Hong Kong on May 17.
